{
  "stem": "20088.9",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Her father was-- when he still had business things to attend to in Indonesia, he was killed on-- in a plane crash.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And so, you know, that was very bad for her, after having survived the wars and being killed that way.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we became good friends.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And I've still been in touch with her very recently.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At the time, it was Kinsberger.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But then she married-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I knew the-- a Jewish boy.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But I've forgotten his name now.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But I've been in-- I knew him as well, quite well.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He looked a bit like Danny Kaye, and we always used to call him Danny.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So his name was something quite different.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] There started to be a little Jewish community, partly people who had come back from different concentration camps and partly, as well, Jews who had been in hiding.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was another Jewish family with three sons-- Solomons.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And their middle son, Hank Solomon, he always came to us.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He liked my mother and it was-- and reminded my mother of Heinz.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we got on very well.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And a lot of young people came to the house from school, but you know, it as not-- we were not a family.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I was really-- there was a very-- instead of being a happy times that I survived, it was a very unhappy time.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that my father and brother hadn't survived is something I couldn't come to terms with at all.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "So we had hit notice from the Red Cross.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I just didn't believe it.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And I was convinced that one day my father would turn up.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And one did hear stories that people who had escaped somewhere and had been in Russia and came back again.",
      "word_count": 20
    }
  ],
